        <clause>
            <title>Chairperson</title>
            <draftingnote>
                <title>Chairperson</title>
                <section1>
                    <para>This wording may not be necessary if the chairman of the company is present at the meeting and
                        is also to chair it. However, it is often included in board minutes for the sake of clarity. In
                        addition, if the chairman of the company is interested in the business to be conducted at the
                        meeting, it may be appropriate for another member of the board to either chair the entire
                        meeting or the part of the meeting in which the chairman is interested. In such circumstances,
                        the minutes should make it clear whether that person is to chair the entire meeting or only a
                        portion of it.
                    </para>
                </section1>
            </draftingnote>
            <para>[NAME] was appointed chairperson of the meeting [and chaired the meeting throughout].</para>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Notice and quorum</title>
            <para>The chairperson reported that due notice of the meeting had been given and that a quorum was present.
                Accordingly, the chairperson declared the meeting open.
            </para>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Interests in proposed transactions and/or arrangements with the Company</title>
            <draftingnote>
                <title>Interests in proposed transactions and/or arrangements with the Company</title>
                <section1>
                    <para>When preparing board minutes for a meeting to approve a proposed transaction or arrangement
                        with the Company, select those paragraphs below that reflect the declarations of interest made
                        by the directors at the meeting. If the board meeting has been convened solely to approve a
                        particular corporate transaction, it may not always be the appropriate place at which to record
                        a director's interest in an existing transaction or arrangement under
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="5-505-5216" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Section 182, Companies Act 2006">
                                    section 182
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        of the Companies Act 2006. Accordingly, specimen wording for a director to declare an interest
                        in an existing transaction or arrangement has been provided separately in
                        <plcxlink>
                            <xlink:locator xlink:href="#a129811" xlink:role="xref"
                                           xlink:title="clause 4 - Interests in existing transactions and/or arrangements with the Company">
                                clause 4
                                <xref link="a129811"></xref>
                            </xlink:locator>
                        </plcxlink>
                        below.
                    </para>
                </section1>
            </draftingnote>
            <subclause1 id="a1034307">
                <para>[[The following directors
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    Each director present] declared the nature and extent of their interest in the proposed transaction
                    [and other arrangements] to be considered at the meeting in accordance with the requirements of
                    section 177 of the Companies Act 2006 and the Company&#x2019;s articles of association, as follows:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <table frame="none" pgwide="1">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="30%"/>
                            <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="70%"/>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para>[NAME]</para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para>[NATURE AND EXTENT OF INTEREST]]</para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis role="bold">AND/OR</emphasis>
                </para>
            </subclause1>
            <draftingnote id="a848160">
                <title>Declaring the nature and extent of the interest</title>
                <section1 id="a640667">
                    <para>Although it is not essential to include a table in the board minutes setting out each
                        director's interests, as
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="7-505-5215" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Section 177, Companies Act 2006">
                                    section 177
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        of the
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="3-503-8567" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Companies Act 2006">Companies Act
                                    2006
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        requires the director to declare both the nature and extent of his interest, including such a
                        table may be helpful in showing that the interests have been properly considered and declared.
                    </para>
                    <para>Note that a director is also required to make a further declaration of interest to correct an
                        inaccuracy in an earlier declaration of interest, or to correct an incomplete earlier
                        declaration (
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="7-505-5215" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Section 177, Companies Act 2006">
                                    section 177(3)
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                            , Companies Act 2006
                        </emphasis>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </section1>
            </draftingnote>
            <subclause1 condition="optional" id="a973313">
                <para>[[NAMES]
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    Each director present] confirmed that they had no direct or indirect interest in any way in the
                    proposed transaction [and other arrangements] to be considered at the meeting which they were
                    required by section 177 of the Companies Act 2006 and the Company&#x2019;s articles of association
                    to disclose.
                </para>
            </subclause1>
            <para>
                <emphasis role="bold">AND/OR</emphasis>
            </para>
            <subclause1 condition="optional" id="a398416">
                <para>There was/were produced to the meeting:</para>
                <subclause2 id="a979695">
                    <para>[a notice of declaration of interest by [NAME] dated [DATE] sent to the other directors of the
                        Company under section 184 of the Companies Act 2006;
                        <emphasis role="bold">AND/OR</emphasis>
                    </para>
                </subclause2>
                <subclause2 id="a1013517">
                    <para>a general notice of declaration of interest by [NAME] dated [DATE] given under section 185 of
                        the Companies Act 2006 to the effect that he [DESCRIBE INTEREST IN SPECIFIED BODY CORPORATE OR
                        CONNECTION WITH SPECIFIED PERSON UNDER S.185(2) COMPANIES ACT 2006] and is to be regarded as
                        interested in any transaction or arrangement that may be made with that [body corporate
                        <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                        person] (<emphasis role="bold">Declaration of Interest</emphasis>). The Declaration of Interest
                        was read out to the meeting and its contents duly noted.]
                    </para>
                </subclause2>
            </subclause1>
            <draftingnote id="a979840">
                <title>Declaration by notice in writing</title>
                <section1 id="a333199">
                    <para>
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="7-505-7691" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Section 184, Companies Act 2006">
                                    Section 184(5)(a)
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        of the Companies Act 2006 provides that the making of a declaration by written notice under
                        section 184 is deemed to form part of the proceedings at the next meeting of the directors after
                        the notice is given, however, it may be good practice to draw the notice to the attention of
                        those directors present at the meeting to ensure that they are all aware of the relevant
                        director's interests.
                    </para>
                </section1>
            </draftingnote>
            <subclause1 id="a208335">
                <para>It was noted that pursuant to article [NUMBER] of the Company's articles of association, [a
                    director may vote and form part of the quorum in relation to any proposed transaction or arrangement
                    in which they are interested[, subject to any restrictions imposed under article [NUMBER] of the
                    Company&#x2019;s articles of association.]
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    the director[s] so interested would not vote or count as part of a quorum on any of the matters in
                    which they were [respectively] interested and that, nevertheless, there would be a quorum for all
                    items of business to be transacted by the meeting.]
                </para>
            </subclause1>
            <draftingnote id="a637430">
                <title>Restrictions on the ability of a director to count towards the quorum and vote</title>
                <section1 id="a106633">
                    <para>It may be the case, where the Company has provisions in its articles of association for
                        dealing with the management of directors' conflict situations, including the terms on which the
                        board may authorise a conflict, that the board has imposed particular restrictions on a director
                        as part of its authorisation of a director's potential conflict. For example, under
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="0-505-5167" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Section 175, Companies Act 2006">
                                    section 175
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        of the Companies Act 2006, the independent directors may decide to authorise a situation whereby
                        a director is also a director of another company if that other interest may be in conflict with
                        the interests of the Company. However, the terms of their authorisation may include a
                        prohibition on the director in question from voting on decisions relating to proposed
                        transactions between the Company and that other company.
                    </para>
                    <para>The wording in square brackets in the third line of
                        <plcxlink>
                            <xlink:locator xlink:href="#a208335" xlink:role="xref"
                                           xlink:title="clause 3.4 - It was noted that pu">paragraph 3.4
                                <xref link="a208335"></xref>
                            </xlink:locator>
                        </plcxlink>
                        highlights that it may not always be the case that a director can vote and form part of the
                        quorum, even where that is provided for under the articles. Consider, in each particular case,
                        whether there are any restrictions that would prevent any of the directors from counting in the
                        quorum or voting on any of the business to be considered at the meeting.
                    </para>
                    <para>See further
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="7-376-3200#a721372" xlink:role="Article"
                                               xlink:title="Skeleton board minutes: drafting note: 1 October 2008: Paragraph 3: Interests in proposed transactions and/or arrangements with the Company">
                                    Drafting note, Skeleton board minutes: Paragraph 3: Interests in proposed
                                    transactions and/or arrangements with the Company
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        .
                    </para>
                </section1>
            </draftingnote>
        </clause>
        <clause condition="optional" id="a129811">
            <title>Interests in existing transactions and/or arrangements with the Company</title>
            <draftingnote>
                <title>Interests in existing transactions and/or arrangements with the Company</title>
                <section1>
                    <para>Include this paragraph if any of the directors are directly or indirectly interested in any
                        existing transaction or arrangement with the Company.
                    </para>
                    <para>Under
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="5-505-5216" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Section 182, Companies Act 2006">
                                    section 182
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        , a director must declare to the other directors the nature and extent of his direct or indirect
                        interest in an existing transaction or arrangement entered into by the Company. Where an earlier
                        declaration becomes inaccurate or incomplete, a further declaration must be made. Section 182
                        does not apply to the extent that the interest has been declared under
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="7-505-5215" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Section 177, Companies Act 2006">
                                    section 177
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        (duty to declare interest in proposed transaction or arrangement). The section also does not
                        apply to transactions or arrangements entered into before 1 October 2008: such interests should
                        instead be declared under section 317 of the
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="2-505-5086" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                               xlink:role="PrimarySource" xlink:title="Companies Act 1985">1985 Act
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        : see
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="5-202-4474" xlink:role="Article"
                                               xlink:title="Declaration of directors' interests: Companies Act 2006">
                                    Declaration of directors' interests: Companies Act 2006: Transitional provisions and
                                    savings
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        and
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="1-383-5040" xlink:role="Article"
                                               xlink:title="Skeleton board minutes: prior to 1 October 2008">Skeleton
                                    board minutes: prior to 1 October 2008: 3. DECLARATIONS OF INTEREST
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        .)
                    </para>
                    <para>For information that must be included in the declaration, see
                        <emphasis role="italic">
                            <plcxlink>
                                <xlink:locator xlink:href="5-202-4474" xlink:role="Article"
                                               xlink:title="Declaration of directors' interests: Companies Act 2006">
                                    Practice note, Declaration of directors' interests: Companies Act 2006
                                </xlink:locator>
                            </plcxlink>
                        </emphasis>
                        .
                    </para>
                </section1>
            </draftingnote>
            <subclause1 id="a555238">
                <para>[The following director[s] declared the nature and extent of [his
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    their] interest(s) in [DESCRIBE EXISTING TRANSACTION AND/OR ARRANGEMENTS] in accordance with the
                    requirements of section 182 of the Companies Act 2006 and the Company&#x2019;s articles of
                    association, as follows:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <table frame="none" pgwide="1">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="30%"/>
                            <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="70%"/>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para>[NAME]</para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para>[NATURE AND EXTENT OF INTEREST]</para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                                        <para></para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis role="bold">AND/OR</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para></para>
            </subclause1>
            <subclause1 id="a78623">
                <para>[There was/were produced to the meeting:</para>
                <subclause2 id="a570784">
                    <para>[a notice of declaration of interest by [NAME] dated [DATE] sent to the other directors of the
                        Company under section 184 of the Companies Act 2006;
                        <emphasis role="bold">AND/OR</emphasis>
                    </para>
                </subclause2>
                <subclause2 id="a812409">
                    <para>a general notice of declaration of interest by [NAME] dated [DATE] given under section 185 of
                        the Companies Act 2006 to the effect that he [DESCRIBE NATURE AND EXTENT OF INTEREST IN
                        SPECIFIED BODY CORPORATE OR FIRM, OR NATURE OF CONNECTION WITH SPECIFIED PERSON UNDER S.185(2)
                        COMPANIES ACT 2006] and is to be regarded as interested in any transaction or arrangement that
                        may be made with that [body corporate
                        <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                        firm
                        <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                        person] (<emphasis role="bold">Declaration of Interest</emphasis>). The Declaration of Interest
                        was read out to the meeting and its contents duly noted.]
                    </para>
                </subclause2>
                <draftingnote>
                    <title>General notices</title>
                    <?Pub Caret -1?>
                    <section1>
                        <para>Although section 182(2) of the Companies Act 2006 provides that the declaration must be
                            made at a meeting of the directors, or by notice in writing (under
                            <emphasis role="italic">
                                <plcxlink>
                                    <xlink:locator xlink:href="7-505-7691" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                                   xlink:role="PrimarySource"
                                                   xlink:title="Section 184, Companies Act 2006">section 184
                                    </xlink:locator>
                                </plcxlink>
                            </emphasis>
                            ), or by general notice (under
                            <emphasis role="italic">
                                <plcxlink>
                                    <xlink:locator xlink:href="8-505-5234" xlink:provider="justcite"
                                                   xlink:role="PrimarySource"
                                                   xlink:title="Section 185, Companies Act 2006">section 185
                                    </xlink:locator>
                                </plcxlink>
                            </emphasis>
                            ), a general notice given under section 185 is only taken to be notice of interests in
                            transactions or arrangements entered into by the Company after the date of the general
                            notice and not notice of an interest existing at the time the notice is given (section
                            185(2)(a) and (b)). However, if a general notice under section 185 is used to declare an
                            interest in an existing transaction as well as future transactions and arrangements with the
                            same company, the directors are likely to be taken to be aware of the director's interest in
                            the existing transaction by virtue of section 182(6)(b) of the Companies Act 2006.
                        </para>
                    </section1>
                </draftingnote>
            </subclause1>
